pr_title: adding the gui terminal to ganga and daemonization
pr_body: run.sh in gui folder works as discussed now working on creating a command to access the terminal easily

Also some thought should be given to how the server process eventually will stop.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 16, 5, 15, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'egede', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 689243885, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
def open_terminal(columns=80, lines=24):
    p_pid, master_fd = pty.fork()
    if p_pid == 0:  # Child.
        argv = shlex.split(command)
        env = dict(TERM="linux", LC_ALL="en_GB.UTF-8",
                   COLUMNS=str(columns), LINES=str(lines))
        env = {**os.environ, **env}
        os.execvpe("bash", ['bash', '-c', 'ganga --webgui'], env)
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 16, 5, 18, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'egede', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 689249386, 'comment_body': 'autotype.py is used to type start ganga gui without user interaction from the web terminal, i was going to use selenium but it

', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 16, 5, 36, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gurudattapatil', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 689254760, 'comment_body': 'actually </dev/null &>/dev/null & provides same functionality as disown process, this will also prevent unwanted logs to be printed.
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 16, 5, 53, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gurudattapatil', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 689256774, 'comment_body': 'No, I do not think so. Also some thought should be given to how the server process eventually will stop.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 16, 5, 15, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'egede', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 689243885, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
def open_terminal(columns=80, lines=24):
    p_pid, master_fd = pty.fork()
    if p_pid == 0:  # Child.
        argv = shlex.split(command)
        env = dict(TERM="linux", LC_ALL="en_GB.UTF-8",
                   COLUMNS=str(columns), LINES=str(lines))
        env = {**os.environ, **env}
        os.execvpe("bash", ['bash', '-c', 'ganga --webgui'], env)
